OL,3,CUnder-16s in England to be banned from
OL,4,Cbuying energy drinks
OL,6,FChildren under 16 in England will be
OL,7,Fbanned from buying high-caffeine
OL,8,Fenergy drinks from April next year,
OL,9,Fthe government has announced.
OL,11,FThe ban will apply to shops, vending
OL,12,Fmachines and online retailers in a bid
OL,13,Fto "protect thousands of children".
OL,15,FProducts containing more than 150mg of
OL,16,Fcaffeine per litre will be made
OL,17,Fillegal for anyone under 16, while
OL,18,Ftea, coffee and soft drinks such as
OL,19,FCoca-Cola and Pepsi are exempt.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
