OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784236711
OL,3,CUnder-16s in England to be banned from
OL,4,Cbuying energy drinks
OL,6,FThe government said this will protect
OL,7,Fchildren's health from the "harms
OL,8,Flinked to high-caffeine energy drinks".
OL,10,FIt's estimated that around 100,000
OL,11,Fchildren in England drink energy
OL,12,Fdrinks high in caffeine every day, and
OL,13,Fevidence suggests this can negatively
OL,14,Fimpact their physical and mental
OL,15,Fhealth, as well as their education.
OL,17,FChildren living in more deprived areas
OL,18,Fand households are more likely to
OL,19,Fconsume these drinks, increasing
OL,20,Fhealth risks and impairing their
OL,21,Flearning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784236711
OL,3,CUnder-16s in England to be banned from
OL,4,Cbuying energy drinks
OL,6,FPublic Health Minister Sharon Hodgson
OL,7,Fsaid: "High-caffeine energy drinks
OL,8,Fhave no place in children's hands. We
OL,9,Fknow thousands of kids in England
OL,10,Fconsume them daily but the evidence is
OL,11,Fclear that this can cause anxiety,
OL,12,Faffect their sleep and concentration
OL,13,Fand can have a detrimental impact on
OL,14,Ftheir education.
OL,16,F"This ban will reduce children's
OL,17,Fopportunity to buy drinks that are
OL,18,Fharmful to their health and wellbeing,
OL,19,Fand demonstrates our firm commitment
OL,20,Fto creating the healthiest generation
OL,21,Fof children ever."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
